@NODE Introduction "What is AMask?"

What is AMask?
--------------

AMask is a Mask-Editor with that you can simple create Masks.
That is: You can AMask as it were how a Paintprogram control, with that you
can create your own surfaces, without that you must insert the Commands self.
(How _PushButton for example) You can use all Elements about the PullDown-Menu
from AMask. A ready Mask can you saving as standard ASCII. This Mask can you
now Loading, with 'Merge asc' from the AMOSPro-Menu, into AMOSPro-Interpreter.
ID-Number, Coordinaates, Colors and all the other parameters are now exact.
With it get the AMOSPro-User a good help to create Buttons.

@ENDNODE


@NODE Short "Short Index of all Options."

Short Index of all Options.
---------------------------

AMask is Compiled as an AMOS-Program and can directly Loaded into the AMOSPro-
Editor. For easy Work, install AMask into the AMOSPro-UserMenu. Now you can
AMask fast start from the Interpreters User-Menu.

All Options of AMask can you getting from the PullDown-Menu.

The 'Project'-Menu
------------------

New:
----
Starts a new Project. The current Mask going lost.

Open:
-----
Opening a Saved Mask (ASCII) into the AMask-Editor for continue Working.

Save & Save as...:
------------------
Saving a Mask (ASCII) to Disk/HD...

Quit:
-----
Quit AMask and going back to the Interpreter.

The 'Edit1'-Menu
----------------

ScreenMode:
-----------
Here you can select the ScreenMode.
(Highres/Lowres/Interlace)

Create:
-------
Here you can create the Elements ScreenBar, WinClone, Mask & Text.

Remove:
-------
Remove a Element that you have create with 'Create'. This option will
always remove the last Element.

The 'Edit2'-Menu
----------------

Create:
-------
Here you can create the Elements PushButton, CheckBox, RadioButton,
CycleButton, ToggleButton, StringGadget & TextGadget.

Remove:
-------
Remove a Element that you have create with 'Create'. You can now clicking
on the Button that you will remove. Click RightMouse to Abort this option.
(Please read the InfoText into the Screenbar)

